scientists. And I think The Book of Why just articulates some of the stuff really well.

00:28:15.119 --> 00:28:20.880
I think what I would boil this down to is that classic phrase that data scientists

00:28:20.880 --> 00:28:27.280
use, which is, is it causation or correlation and how we mix up those things? And

00:28:28.640 --> 00:28:35.520
at one extreme, you have purely observational correlational data. And at the other extreme,

00:28:36.239 --> 00:28:40.959
you have randomized controlled trials, like really well-controlled experiments.

00:28:41.520 --> 00:28:45.359
And then you've got a spectrum. There's a spectrum of stuff between that.

00:28:46.079 --> 00:28:52.160
